        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 31 at 8:50AM EDT by NWS Wilmington OH</headline>
        <description>At 850 AM EDT, a strong thunderstorm was located 9 miles north of
Harrison, moving east at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and very heavy rain.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Visibility will be poor and hydroplaning
is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Cincinnati, Hamilton, Middletown, Fairfield, Covington, Oxford,
Forest Park, Erlanger, Sharonville, Monroe, Trenton, Springdale,
Harrison, North College Hill, Wyoming, Cheviot, Fort Mitchell, Villa
Hills, Mount Healthy, and Fort Wright.

This includes the following Interstates...
I-71 in Ohio between mile markers 0 and 4.
I-74 in Indiana between mile markers 159 and 171.
I-74 in Ohio between mile markers 0 and 19.
I-75 in Kentucky between mile markers 186 and 191.
I-75 in Ohio between mile markers 0 and 10, and between mile markers
16 and 19.

If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a sturdy building.

Motorists should slow down and use extra caution.

To report hazardous weather conditions, go to our website at
weather.gov/iln and submit your report via social media, when you can
do so safely.
</description>
